TailCloud (opencloud self-hosted with full encryption in tailscale VPN)

1) Install tailscale on the host -->https://tailscale.com/kb/1031/install-linux
curl -fsSL https://tailscale.com/install.sh | sh

2) Follow the guide for Getting Started-Classic Docker setup until Step 3 --> https://github.com/opencloud-eu/docs/blob/main/docs/admin/20-getting-started/30-docker.md#3--initialize-opencloud-first-time-setup
It is necessary to initialize OpenCloud! And only ONE Time!

3)change into directory for the certs
cd $HOME/opencloud/opencloud-data/proxy

4) get ssl certs for your opencloud-server
tailscale cert opencloud.TAILSCALEDOMAIN.ts.net
mv server.* server_old.* 
rename the TailScale CRT and KEY file to server.crt and server.key

5) Go ahead to step 4 -->https://github.com/opencloud-eu/docs/blob/main/docs/admin/20-getting-started/30-docker.md#4-start-opencloud 

Change 2 lines:
 -e OC_INSECURE=true \  -->  -e OC_INSECURE=false \
 -e OC_URL=https://localhost:9200 \ -->  -e OC_URL=https://opencloud.YOURTAILSCALEDOMAIN.ts.net:9200 \ 

6) Open a browser and go to:
https://opencloud.YOURTAILSCALEDOMAIN.ts.net:9200

7) ThatÂ´s all ... for nowðŸ˜„

